.TH "rcu_sync_enter_start" 9 "rcu_sync_enter_start" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rcu_sync_enter_start \- Force readers onto slow path for multiple updates
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rcu_sync_enter_start
.BI "(struct rcu_sync *rsp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rsp" 12
Pointer to rcu_sync structure to use for synchronization
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Must be called after \fBrcu_sync_init\fP and before first use.

Ensures \fBrcu_sync_is_idle\fP returns false and rcu_sync_{enter,exit}()
pairs turn into NO-OPs.
